# NHANES-ClinicoMetrics

## Project Overview

This project analyzes cardiovascular risk factors using data from the National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES).

The analysis was conducted in R using tidyverse, ggplot2, and statistical modeling techniques commonly used in epidemiological research.

## Dataset

Source: NHANES (National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey)

Final analytical sample:

- 4,424 unique adult participants
- Adults aged 20 years and older
- Participants with valid blood pressure measurements

## Methods

The analysis included:

- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- BMI classification using WHO guidelines
- Hypertension classification using AHA guidelines
- Data visualization using ggplot2
- Welch two-sample t-test
- Multiple linear regression
- Logistic regression

## Key Findings

- Higher age was associated with higher systolic blood pressure.
- Higher BMI was associated with higher systolic blood pressure.
- The prevalence of hypertension increased across BMI categories.
- No significant difference in cholesterol levels was observed between smokers and non-smokers in this sample.

